           Summary        
                                    
                                       
                                                                 
        Throughout history there have been sightings of a massive     
        Octopus big enough to attack and sink boats. Could such a     
        creature really exist? Our divers probe the depths of the     
        North Pacific where the worlds largest known species of      
        octopus lives. Could these octopuses be a food source for     
        a monster? The investigation will use various underwater      
        camera systems, including a tiny camera small enough to       
        probe inside octopus lairs. Deep waters, rough currents,      
        freezing temperatures and the prospect of encountering a      
         20-ton boneless horror make this a dangerous expedition.
